' ============================================================================
' Diagram template — copy this file, drop it under the right folder
' (architecture/, sequences/, make/, …), rename it, and replace the body.
'
' This file is **not rendered**: anything under `docs/uml/include/` is
' skipped by `scripts/regenerate_docs.py`.
'
' Conventions inherited from `include/style.puml` (auto-injected after
' `@startuml`):
'   - Palette tokens: `$BG_*`, `$BORDER_*`, `$INK_*`. Reuse them, never
'     paste raw hex into a diagram.
'   - Element semantics: blue = application/API, orange = persistence,
'     emerald = actor, violet = queue, slate = neutral infra.
'   - Notes inherit calm amber styling — no need to colour them manually.
'   - Macros: `$Subtitle("…")`, `$Footer("…")`, `$Hint("…")`,
'     `$LegendStandard()`. Opt-in; skip when the title is enough.
'
' Layout direction:
'   - Architecture / containers / components → `top to bottom direction`
'   - Sequences → keep participant order consistent across sibling diagrams
'     (Integrator → HTTP API → Service → SchedulePolicy → DB)
' ============================================================================

@startuml
title ETR Study API — <one-line scope of this diagram>
$Subtitle("optional caption — version, ADR link, or owning team")

top to bottom direction

' --- Participants / containers --------------------------------------------
actor    "Integrator"        as Client
rectangle "ETR Study API"    as Api
database "Relational store"  as Db

' --- Relationships ---------------------------------------------------------
Client --> Api : HTTPS · JSON
Api    --> Db  : SQL · transactions

' --- Optional chrome -------------------------------------------------------
' $LegendStandard()
' $Footer("ADR-0020 · uml/include/style.puml")

@enduml

' ============================================================================
' Sequence-diagram skeleton (keep participant order consistent across files)
' ============================================================================
'
' @startuml
' title ETR Study API — <flow name>
' autonumber
' hide footbox
'
' actor       "Integrator"        as Client
' boundary    "HTTP API"          as Api
' control     "ConspectusService" as Service
' participant "SchedulePolicy"    as Policy
' database    "DB (transaction)"  as Db
'
' Client -> Api : POST /api/v1/...
' activate Api
'   Api -> Service : call
'   activate Service
'     alt happy path
'       Service -> Db : INSERT
'       Service --> Api : DTO
'       Api --> Client : 201 Created
'     else error
'       Service --> Api : 409
'       Api --> Client : 409
'     end
'   deactivate Service
' deactivate Api
' @enduml
'
' ============================================================================
' State-machine skeleton
' ============================================================================
'
' @startuml
' title <name> — state machine
'
' [*] --> Idle : start condition
' Idle    : entry actions go here
' Active  : entry actions go here
'
' Idle    --> Active  : trigger
' Active  --> Idle    : reset trigger
' Active  --> [*]     : terminal trigger
' @enduml
'
' ============================================================================
' Activity-diagram skeleton
' ============================================================================
'
' @startuml
' title <name> — decision flow
'
' start
' :first action;
' if (condition?) then (yes)
'   :branch A;
' else (no)
'   :branch B;
' endif
' :join action;
' stop
' @enduml
